text: Chen Szu-yu (; born 1 August 1993) is a Taiwanese table tennis player. She competed for Chinese Taipei at the 2012, 2016, and 2020 Summer Olympics. Chen is a two-time medalist at the World Team Championships as a member of the Chinese Taipei women's team. ==References== ==External links== * * * * Category:1993 births Category:Living people Category:People with ankylosing spondylitis Category:Table tennis players
